comments.content: "male soprano, described as the boy with a million dollar voice"
"male soprano"; "Direct from six months in Cincinnati . . ."; actually unnamed here, but see Zanesville OH Signal, July 17, 1938, A2
character dancer; "Billy Allen" but guessing that this is the same Bobby Allen that appeared two weeks later.
"who closely resembles the late Jean Harlow"

No indication whether he was present but adding to make clear connections
